"""
Submit_2.py
===========
Core calculation engine.  Called by UI_2.py → perform_calculation_2().

Design notes
------------
*  All "find column for this month" calls are centralised to the two helpers
   find_columns_with_month_short / find_columns_with_month_long from the
   helper module.  No inline column-index arithmetic elsewhere.

*  Formula strings that reference external workbooks are built by
   generate_excel_formula() which always uses forward-slash paths.  This is
   the root cause of the "broken links" bug in the original code:
   openpyxl's load_workbook() + save() without keep_links=True strips the
   external relationship entries from the zip package.  The fix is applied
   inside paste_values_KPI_PL (keep_links=True).

*  All helper imports are explicit so the linter can resolve them.
"""

